
$ Validation: Free-free beam — rigid body modes (SOL 103)
$ A completely unconstrained beam must have exactly 6 zero-frequency modes,
$ corresponding to 3 rigid-body translations and 3 rigid-body rotations.
$
$ Geometry:  L = 10 m, 10 equal CBAR elements (1 m each), 11 nodes
$ Material:  Steel — E = 200 GPa, nu = 0.3, rho = 7850 kg/m^3
$ Section:   Solid square, side = 0.31623 m
$              A  = 0.1 m^2
$              I1 = I2 = a^4/12 = 8.333e-4 m^4
$ BCs:       None — free-free (no SPC)
$
$ Expected:  Modes 1–6:  f ≈ 0 Hz  (rigid body modes)
$            Mode  7 onwards: elastic bending / torsion modes
$ Notes:     Numerical rigid-body frequencies will be small but non-zero
$            (typically < 1e-3 Hz or eigenvalue < 1e-5 rad^2/s^2).
$            Solver must NOT crash on a singular or near-singular stiffness matrix.
$ Units:     SI (m, N, kg, Pa)
$
SOL 103
$
SUBCASE 1
  TITLE  = Free-Free Beam — Rigid Body Mode Check
  METHOD = 20
$
BEGIN BULK
$
$ ------------------------------------------------------------------ NODES
$ GRID, GID, CP, X1,  X2,  X3, CD, PS, SEID
GRID,  1, , 0.0,  0.0, 0.0
GRID,  2, , 1.0,  0.0, 0.0
GRID,  3, , 2.0,  0.0, 0.0
GRID,  4, , 3.0,  0.0, 0.0
GRID,  5, , 4.0,  0.0, 0.0
GRID,  6, , 5.0,  0.0, 0.0
GRID,  7, , 6.0,  0.0, 0.0
GRID,  8, , 7.0,  0.0, 0.0
GRID,  9, , 8.0,  0.0, 0.0
GRID, 10, , 9.0,  0.0, 0.0
GRID, 11, , 10.0, 0.0, 0.0
$
$ --------------------------------------------------------------- MATERIAL
$ MAT1, MID, E,      G,        NU,  RHO
MAT1, 1, 2.0e11, 7.692e10, 0.3, 7850.0
$
$ ------------------------------------------------------------- PROPERTIES
$ PBAR, PID, MID, A,   I1,       I2,       J
$ Solid square: a = 0.31623 m
PBAR, 1, 1, 0.1, 8.333e-4, 8.333e-4, 1.406e-3
$ +,   C1,      C2,       D1,       D2,       E1,        E2,       F1,       F2
+,    0.15811, 0.15811, -0.15811, 0.15811, -0.15811, -0.15811, 0.15811, -0.15811
$
$ --------------------------------------------------------------- ELEMENTS
$ CBAR, EID, PID, GA, GB, X1,  X2,  X3
$ Orientation vector (0,1,0): local y = global Y
CBAR,  1, 1,  1,  2, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
CBAR,  2, 1,  2,  3, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
CBAR,  3, 1,  3,  4, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
CBAR,  4, 1,  4,  5, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
CBAR,  5, 1,  5,  6, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
CBAR,  6, 1,  6,  7, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
CBAR,  7, 1,  7,  8, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
CBAR,  8, 1,  8,  9, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
CBAR,  9, 1,  9, 10, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
CBAR, 10, 1, 10, 11, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
$
$ ----------------------------------------------------------- CONSTRAINTS
$ No SPC — beam is completely free (free-free)
$
$ --------------------------------------------------------- EIGENVALUE METHOD
$ EIGRL, SID, V1, V2, ND, MSGLVL, MAXSET, SHFSCL, NORM
$ Extract 12 modes: first 6 are rigid body (~0 Hz), next 6 are elastic
EIGRL, 20, , , 12, , , , MASS
$
ENDDATA
